Ask HN: Those making $500/month on side projects in 2023 – Where you find users?
text: As an indie app developer making $30-$50 per month on side projects, I'm curious to hear your strategies for finding new users. Do you rely on word-of-mouth or have you found success leveraging social media platforms like Twitter? Have you experimented with paid ads? For now most users find my apps with App Store search and I don't feel I have any control over it.

Ask HN: What to do when your technical ineptitude is hurting startup progress?
text:
Hi everyone,

Harj Taggar said in a YC YouTube video that you should learn an adequate level technical skill sufficient to build an MVP yourself.

I have done that to the best of my ability, but I cannot learn fast enough about each aspect of my product to maintain a healthy speed for iteration and improvement. I feel like hiring someone would be like lighting a very short fuse (I could afford to do that only for about 2-3 months), but by myself I am moving so slow I can't keep up with user feedback.

Speed or a longer runway. Which is more valuable?

Thanks!

Show HN: A no-code canvas for financial planning, model various scenarios
text:
I built this no-code tool for modelling personal finance situations. The idea is to democratize financial modelling by allowing people without knowledge of Excel or being an expert to understand and model financial matters. Does this idea makes sense to you? Please feel free to try it out. No login is required and no data is sent to a server. haha, there is no backend at all!

Built on top of Excalidraw canvas with financial modelling done on the client with JS.
